# Global .graphifyignore template - privacy + noise guard
# Usage: copy/symlink to the repo root before the first /graphify .
# Works like .gitignore - rules can be overridden in the repo's own .graphifyignore

# === Privacy (CRITICAL, never in graph) ===
PROMPTS.md
SKILLS_LOG.md
CLAUDE.local.md
.claude/state/
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/plans/
.env*
credentials*
*_token*
*_secret*
*api_key*
*apikey*
*password*
.ssh/
.aws/
.gnupg/
*.pem
*.key
id_rsa*

# === Graphify self-exclusion (prevent recursive extraction) ===
AGENTS.md
CLAUDE.md
GEMINI.md
.gemini/
.opencode/
graphify-out/
docs/translations/

# === Build/deps (noise, no semantics) ===
node_modules/
dist/
build/
.venv/
venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
target/
.next/
.nuxt/
coverage/
.coverage

# === VCS / tooling ===
.git/
